title: Héctor Pedraza Olguín
content:
Héctor Pedraza Olguín (born 30 August 1966) is a Mexican politician from the Institutional Revolutionary Party (PRI). From 2009 to 2012 he served as a federal deputy in the 61st Congress, representing 
Hidalgo's second district.[1]

This article about an Institutional Revolutionary Party politician born in the 1960s who served in the Chamber of Deputies is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.
